description: From Latin obtendere, obtentum (“to stretch or place before or against”), from ob (see ob-) + tendere (“to stretch”).

verbs.description: obtend (third-person singular simple present obtends, present participle obtending, simple past and past participle obtended)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To oppose; to hold out in opposition.
(obsolete) To offer as the reason for something; to pretend.
